One Hamisu Ahmed, on Saturday got drowned in an open water well at Samegu behind Sahad, Kano State. NAN reports that Fire Service Public Relations Officer, Saminu Abdullahi, who confirmed the incident said that the victim was a 20-year-old mechanic who went to take his bath after repairing a car. Abdullahi said at about 07:31am, it received a distress call from one Muhammad Abdulmalik. “On receiving the information, we quickly sent our rescue team to the scene at about 07:43 am,” he said. Abdullahi added that Hamisu was brought out of the water dead and his corpse was handed over to his father, Alhaji Yahaya Usman of Dorayi Chiranci Quarters.